OL,3,CGrieving mother shares her story to
OL,4,Chighlight importance of vaccination
OL,6,F"Heartbreaking seeing him lying in the
OL,7,Fhospital bed, so tiny and so
OL,8,Fhelpless," Maureen recalls.
OL,10,F"I said the doctors and nurses are
OL,11,Fgoing to make you all better. But
OL,12,Funfortunately, that wasn't to be.
OL,14,F"We could see the red dots of the rash
OL,15,Fappearing on his skin. And then he
OL,16,Fjust held his thumb up and said 'Sore
OL,17,FMommy' and I kissed it and said we're
OL,18,Fgoing to the doctors and nurses are
OL,19,Fgoing to make you all better. But
OL,20,Funfortunately, that wasn't to be."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1777745466
OL,3,CGrieving mother shares her story to
OL,4,Chighlight importance of vaccination
OL,6,FAt the time David became ill, a
OL,7,Fvaccine for his strain of meningitis
OL,8,Fwas not available. It was introduced
OL,9,Fin 2015.
OL,11,FAccording to the Public Health Agency,
OL,12,FMenB vaccinations in Northern Ireland
OL,13,Fare sitting over 85% among two-year-
OL,14,Folds. That's below what recommended
OL,15,Flevels. WHO says a 95% vaccination
OL,16,Frate is needed to prevent outbreaks.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
